This paper presents a robotic navigation algorithm that combines natural language processing, motion planning, and computer vision to enable a robot to safely navigate through a changing environment with moving persons by following human instructions. The paper focuses on the development of a system that can successfully follow natural language navigation instructions to achieve navigation tasks in both simulated and real-world scenarios. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is Robotics (cs.RO), followed by Computational Linguistics and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC).
